headlines.headline: Hank Haney: Record pursuit taxed Tiger

related.title: Tiger Woods critical of Hank Haney writing book
Tiger Woods' ex-swing coach Hank Haney to publish book

headlines.title:
Tiger Woods' pursuit of Jack Nicklaus' record took a toll,
             ex-swing coach writes
headlines.linkText: Haney: Tiger's pursuit of Nicklaus took a toll
headlines.description:
Tiger Woods' quest to break Jack Nicklaus' record of 18 major championships weighed heavily on the former world No. 1 golfer,
             his former swing coach,
             Hank Haney,
             said in a book excerpt released Tuesday.

headlines.headline: Donald Trump buys Doral for $150M
headlines.title: Donald Trump buying Doral Hotel & Country Club for $150 million
headlines.linkText:
Trump buys Doral golf course,
             hotel for $150M
headlines.description:
Donald Trump is buying the Doral Hotel & Country Club,
             home of the Blue Monster golf course and host to numerous professional tournaments over the years,
             for $150 million.

headlines.headline: 'Yippy' Rankin honored at memorial
headlines.title:
Walter 'Yippy' Rankin,
             husband of LPGA Hall of Famer Judy Rankin,
             dies at 71
headlines.linkText:
'Yippy' Rankin,
             husband of Judy,
             dies at 71
headlines.description:
Walter "Yippy" Rankin,
             the husband of golf analyst Judy Rankin,
             died last week and was honored at a memorial service in Texas on Monday.

headlines.headline: Skip Kendall wins with long birdie on 18
headlines.title: Skip Kendall wins Nationwide Tour opener with long birdie on 18
headlines.linkText: Kendall wins Nationwide with long birdie on 18
headlines.description: Skip Kendall holed a 25-foot birdie putt on the final hole Sunday for an even-par 71 and a one-stroke victory in the Nationwide Tour's season-opening Colombia Championship.

headlines.headline: Bill Haas wins at Riviera in playoff

related.title: Phil Mickelson takes wild ride into share of the lead at Northern Trust Open

headlines.title:
Bill Haas edges Phil Mickelson,
             Keegan Bradley on second playoff hole
headlines.linkText:
Haas edges Lefty,
             Bradley on 2nd playoff hole
headlines.description:
Bill Haas knows anything is possible from even the most dire positions. Remember,
             this is the guy only five months ago saved par with his ball partially submerged in a lake and won the FedEx Cup.

images.name: Haas Wins At Riviera In Playoff
images.caption:
